The man has appeared in the Wynberg Magistrates Court after his arrest earlier this week on crimen injuria charges. CAPE TOWN A University of Cape Town employee has been suspended for allegedly filming and livestreaming a colleague while she expressed breastmilk in a campus office.The woman has also laid criminal charges against him.The man has appeared in the Wynberg Magistrates Court after his arrest earlier this week on crimen injuria charges.UCT spokesperson Elijah Moholola said: UCT confirms that there was a disturbing incident that took place on campus earlier this month. And out of that a process was set underway to deal with this incident in terms of disciplinary processes that are in place. 